<div class="col-md-9 col-sm-8">
<h4 class="montserrat gold coach">Sprints Coach - Martin Cook</h4>
<p>

Hi, my name is Martin Cook and I am the sprints coach for University of Sheffield Athletics Club. I am a fully qualified level 2 coach for Sprints and Hurdles and began coaching for the University in September 2011, although I do have many years worth of coaching experience. I also still train and compete as an athlete in 400m where I have medalled at Regional level and competed at National Championships indoor and out.<br><br>

My coaching philosophy is very simple;<br><br>

Work as hard as you can in training and you will gain the rewards in competition!<br>

Athletes at my sessions will work hard but I’m sure that they will all (mostly) tell you that they will have fun along the way. If you work hard for me then I’ll work hard for you! Remember, “Pain is just weakness leaving the body!”



</p>
